<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;We are doomed to die!&quot; he said to his wife.  &quot;We have seen God!&quot;<br>
But his wife answered, &quot;If the Lord had meant to kill us, he would not have accepted a burnt offering and grain offering from our hands, nor shown us all these things or now told us this.&quot; - Judges 13:22-23<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, I guess we can see that Samson got his lack of common sense from his father.  (Since later Samson showed a lack of common sense when telling his wife that cutting his hair would make him lose his strength.  I would think a wise man would find her questioning him on such things a tad suspicious.)  &quot;Yes honey, please tell me how to kill you.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Suppose this black pit of a kingdom of yours is the only world.  Well, it strikes me as a pretty poor one.  And that's a funny thing, when you come to think of it.  We're just babies making up a game, if you're right.  But four babies playing a game can make a play-world which licks your real world hollow.&quot; - Puddleglum (The Silver Chair)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wordwolf>WordWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sir WordWolf,<br>Keeper of Odd Knowledge,<br>Bachelor-at-Arms</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#B87333>(9/9/03 6:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Humor and the Bible?</span><hr size=1> I thought that was kind-of funny, also.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that, after the first Passover, the belief <br>
seemed to go around that seeing the angel of the Lord<br>
meant you would die.  Seems to me that it's why angels<br>
starting with &quot;Fear not&quot; rather than &quot;hello&quot; as a standard<br>
salutation. <br>
<br>
So, he was fixated on &quot;we're gonna die!&quot; and missed<br>
everything the angel told him-a several-year set of<br>
instructions.<br>
<br>
=======================================<br>
<br>
Yes, after the first time Samson snowed Delilah, and she<br>
betrayed him to the opposing army who wanted to kill<br>
him (and they would have killed him if he had told the <br>
truth), I would have given her the &quot;Ralph Kramden&quot; <br>
 treatment, and she would have been the first woman on<br>
the moon.   I'm a wee bit more pragmatic about things like<br>
that than Samson.  <br>
<br>
==========================================<br>
That stuff isn't what I found to be the funniest thing in<br>
the Bible.  Read the entire story of Balaam sometime. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
